ce:section.ce:para:
The surface functional groups of the N and S co-doped CDs was analyzed by FTIR spectroscopy. The FTIR spectra of both o-CDs and u-CDs revealed the presence of almost the same functional groups (Fig. 4
                           ). The OH and NH stretching vibrations in the region of 2800–3440cm−1 indicated the presence of hydroxyl and amino groups, which contribute to the highly hydrophilic nature of CDs [30–33]. The weak band observed at 2340cm−1 was assigned to CN and SH bond, and the strong bands at 1700 and 1300cm−1 are ascribed to the CO and CO stretching vibrations of the carbonyl and carbonyl groups, respectively [34,35]. The other band related to the CS and CN stretching vibrations is also shown in 1235cm−1 
                           [29,36,37].
